Answer: The data files are distributed as .csv.gz files instead of .csv files because the .csv.gz files are compressed and take up less space.The â.gzâ extension indicates that the file is compressed using gzip compression. Compressing files reduces their size, making them quicker to download, upload, and store.

  1. Briefly describe what Bash commands zcat, zless, zmore, and zgrep do.

Answer: zcat is used to display the contents of a compressed file. zless is used to display the contents of a compressed file one page at a time. It is useful for navigating through large compressed files without having to decompress them first.zmore is used to display the contents of a compressed file one page at a time. zgrep is used to search for a pattern in a compressed file.

Q4. Whoâs popular in Price and Prejudice

  1. You and your friend just have finished reading Pride and Prejudice by Jane Austen. Among the four main characters in the book, Elizabeth, Jane, Lydia, and Darcy, your friend thinks that Darcy was the most mentioned. You, however, are certain it was Elizabeth. Obtain the full text of the novel from http://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/42671/pg42671.txt and save to your local folder.
wget -nc http://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/42671/pg42671.txt

Explain what wget -nc does. Do not put this text file pg42671.txt in Git.

Answer: wget -nc downloads the file from the given URL and saves it in the current directory using the same name as the original filename. The -nc option prevents overwriting of existing files.

Complete the following loop to tabulate the number of times each of the four characters is mentioned using Linux commands.

for char in Elizabeth Jane Lydia Darcy
do
  echo $char:
  grep -o -i "$char" pg42671.txt | wc -l
done
  1. Whatâs the difference between the following two commands?
echo 'hello, world' > test1.txt

and

echo 'hello, world' >> test2.txt

Answer: The first command creates a new file test1.txt and writes the string hello, world to it, providing a fresh start with the specified content.

The second command appends the string hello, world to the end of the file test2.txt, preserving any existing content in the file. In this case, it creates a new file because it doesnât exist.

  1. Using your favorite text editor (e.g., vi), type the following and save the file as middle.sh:
#!/bin/sh
# Select lines from the middle of a file.
# Usage: bash middle.sh filename end_line num_lines
head -n "$2" "$1" | tail -n "$3"

Using chmod to make the file executable by the owner, and run

cd ~/203b_hw_new
./middle.sh hw1/pg42671.txt 20 5

Explain the output. Explain the meaning of "$1", "$2", and "$3" in this shell script. Why do we need the first line of the shell script?

Answer: The output is the 5 lines starting from line 20 of the file pg42671.txt. "$1", "$2", and "$3" are the first, second, and third arguments passed to the shell script. The first line of the shell script is needed to tell the shell which program to use to run the script.
